1. System/Technical Requirements
| Requirement      | Description                                                           |
| ---------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Google Colab** | Cloud-based development environment where you run all your code       |
| **Python 3.x**   | Programming language used for ML, preprocessing, and visualization    |
| **CSV Dataset**  | Input dataset (`employee_data.csv`) with employee profiles and salary |

2. Python Libraries (Software Requirements)
| Library                    | Purpose                                                             |
| -------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `pandas`                   | Load, clean, and manipulate tabular data                            |
| `numpy`                    | Perform numerical operations                                        |
| `scikit-learn`             | Preprocess data, build ML models, evaluate predictions              |
| `matplotlib`               | Create visualizations (e.g., scatter plots for actual vs predicted) |
| `joblib`                   | Save and load trained models                                        |
| `streamlit`                | Build and deploy a simple web app interface                         |


3.Functional Requirements

| Feature                     | Description                                                    |
| --------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Data preprocessing          | Convert text labels to encoded formats; scale numerical values |
| Model training              | Train a regression model to predict salary                     |
| Model evaluation            | Measure accuracy using RÂ² score, RMSE, or MAE                  |
| Real-time salary prediction | Predict salary for new inputs after model is trained           |
| Salary adjustment           | Modify dataset salaries to reflect Indian market               |
                                                    

